<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-09-11T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-09-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="134" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d134">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/67<hi rend="superscript">5/24</hi>: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gade</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                                Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-11T17:00:00-06:00">September 11, 1940—5 p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8
                                        p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>45. For General Strong. Permission granted by Salvadoran
                                    Government for photographic air mission to operate in this
                                    country based on San Salvador. Strongly urge that both Honduran
                                    and Salvadoran aviators be given some instruction in methods and
                                    equipment used. Mathewson.</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gade</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>